Reactive Oxygen Species (ROS) are continuously generated by plants under normal conditions. However, they are increased in response to different abiotic stresses. One of the most important effects of climate change-related stresses at the molecular level is the increase of ROS inside the cells ( Farnese et al., 2016). Among ROS, the most studied are superoxide anion (
O 2 •–
), H 2O 2 and the hydroxyl radical (⋅OH -).
